nah-nahs, and hoo-hoos.

254
00:12:13,232 --> 00:12:14,859
This time, we're using the real words.

255
00:12:14,942 --> 00:12:19,363
[hip-hop beat playing]

256
00:12:19,989 --> 00:12:20,823
Hey, Funyun.

257
00:12:20,906 --> 00:12:23,367
-Yeah, Funyun?
-What do you want to do now?

258
00:12:24,452 --> 00:12:27,204
Well, there's something
I normally do with Nate,

259
00:12:27,288 --> 00:12:30,166
but I think it'd be
so much more fun with you.

260
00:12:30,249 --> 00:12:34,712
["Here Comes the Hot Stepper" playing]

261
00:12:34,795 --> 00:12:36,714
<i>-♪ Here comes the hot stepper ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Murderer ♪</i>

262
00:12:36,797 --> 00:12:39,049
-[shutter clicking]
-♪ <i>I'm the lyrical gangster ♪</i>

263
00:12:39,133 --> 00:12:41,844
<i>-♪ Pick up the crew in de area ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Murderer ♪</i>

264
00:12:41,927 --> 00:12:44,263
<i>-♪ Still love you like that ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Murderer… ♪</i>

265
00:12:44,346 --> 00:12:46,098
[shutter clicking]

266
00:12:52,104 --> 00:12:53,189
[song fades out]

267
00:12:55,024 --> 00:12:56,567
Okay, say it back to me, Leia.

268
00:12:56,650 --> 00:12:58,736
[sighs] I can't with the real words.

269
00:12:58,819 --> 00:13:00,988
Okay, whatever you're comfortable with.

270
00:13:01,572 --> 00:13:05,367
Once a nay-nay's been in a nah-nah,
it can't go in a hoo-hoo.

271
00:13:06,327 --> 00:13:08,829
Wait, which one was the nay-nay again?
You know what?

272
00:13:08,913 --> 00:13:11,707
Don't put anything
into anything after it's been in anything.

273
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:14,794
Mom, we really didn't need to go this far.

274
00:13:14,877 --> 00:13:18,047
There's a boy I like, and, yeah,
I've had some thoughts about him.

275
00:13:18,130 --> 00:13:20,633
Like, he's got this one T-shirt
that rides up a little…

276
00:13:21,133 --> 00:13:23,636
I'm jealous, Mom.
I want to be the T-shirt.

277
00:13:25,304 --> 00:13:26,597
Oh, it's happening!

278
00:13:26,680 --> 00:13:29,391
It's not happening.
I haven't even kissed him yet.

279
00:13:30,518 --> 00:13:32,686
Okay, well, have you told him
how you feel?

280
00:13:32,770 --> 00:13:33,604
Sort of.

281
00:13:34,271 --> 00:13:37,399
[sighs] It's kind of a big mess.
I'm so bad at this.

282
00:13:37,483 --> 00:13:39,151
It runs in the family.

283
00:13:39,735 --> 00:13:42,279
-You too?
-Me? No. Your dad.

284
00:13:44,865 --> 00:13:48,410
But no matter how many times
he messed it all up,

285
00:13:49,370 --> 00:13:52,331
I always found my way back to him…
because he has a good heart.

286
00:13:54,124 --> 00:13:55,501
Just like you.

287
00:13:56,627 --> 00:13:58,921
Wait, so Dad wasn't as smooth
as he says he was.

288
00:14:00,339 --> 00:14:02,299
Let's just say, you're lucky you exist.

289
00:14:03,008 --> 00:14:05,928
[rock music playing]

290
00:14:09,682 --> 00:14:11,559
I just feel so lost, Marion.

291
00:14:12,059 --> 00:14:13,435
I don't know who I am anymore.

292
00:14:13,519 --> 00:14:16,689
I went through the same thing
when I lost Ralph.

293
00:14:16,772 --> 00:14:18,566
My whole world turned upside down.

294
00:14:19,441 --> 00:14:21,110
I'm so there, Mar.

295
00:14:22,111 --> 00:14:24,321
But you can adapt. You move on.

296
00:14:24,405 --> 00:14:26,574
Life has more surprises waiting for you.

297
00:14:27,741 --> 00:14:28,742
That's deep.

298
00:14:29,702 --> 00:14:33,038
That's basically what I said
but without the dead husband stuff.

299
00:14:33,122 --> 00:14:34,164
Grandma! No!

300
00:14:34,248 --> 00:14:36,584
I told you to stop tricking guys
into your hot tub.

301
00:14:37,334 --> 00:14:40,963
Wha… She didn't do that. We're just
trying it out before we take it.

302
00:14:41,046 --> 00:14:43,591
Bro, I think that's the trick.

303
00:14:45,509 --> 00:14:49,138
I've got a free king-size bed upstairs
if you'd like to try that out.

304
00:14:49,972 --> 00:14:51,265
-It's free?
-Bro!

305
00:14:57,062 --> 00:15:00,065
-Sorry she wasted your time.
-No, it wasn't a waste.

306
00:15:00,149 --> 00:15:02,943
I was getting down on myself,
and she gave me really good advice.

307
00:15:03,027 --> 00:15:05,195
Yeah, she always helps out the cute ones.

308
00:15:06,447 --> 00:15:08,240
I am reporting you to the <i>Pennysaver.</i>

309
00:15:08,324 --> 00:15:09,909
Ooh!

310
00:15:09,992 --> 00:15:13,829
[funky rock music playing]

311
00:15:14,413 --> 00:15:18,083
Sorry your big moment
was hijacked by my very chill family.

312
00:15:18,876 --> 00:15:20,294
It's fine.

313
00:15:20,377 --> 00:15:22,880
On the way home, I told a crossing guard,
just to stay sharp.

314
00:15:24,131 --> 00:15:26,884
Okay. Brace yourself for some sap.

315
00:15:27,968 --> 00:15:30,012
Thank you for covering for me yesterday.

316
00:15:30,095 --> 00:15:32,473
You didn't have to do it,
but it really meant a lot.

317
00:15:33,474 --> 00:15:34,516
Of course, Ozzie.

318
00:15:35,017 --> 00:15:37,561
You kind of threw me under the bus
with the penis stuff,

319
00:15:37,645 --> 00:15:39,480
but I'll chalk that up to nerves.

320
00:15:40,481 --> 00:15:43,275
I panicked, and that's
what I was thinking about, so I said it.

321
00:15:43,359 --> 00:15:44,485
[soft knocking]

322
00:15:44,568 --> 00:15:46,820
All right, Le-Le, I'm out of here.

323
00:15:46,904 --> 00:15:49,907
It's gonna take me twice as long
if I can only use the real lanes.

324
00:15:49,990 --> 00:15:52,242
-Okay, Mom. Love you.
-Love you.

325
00:15:53,661 --> 00:15:55,746
-Nice to meet you, Ozzie.
-You too.

326
00:15:55,829 --> 00:15:57,748
I can see where Leia gets her good looks.

327
00:15:57,831 --> 00:15:59,833
Oh! You're a little charmer.

328
00:16:00,793 --> 00:16:02,211
You sure you aren't gonna have sex?

329
00:16:02,294 --> 00:16:04,046
-Positive.
-A million percent.

330
00:16:06,674 --> 00:16:09,051
Just hit enter
and you'll be signed in to your email.

331
00:16:09,134 --> 00:16:11,470
[rhythmic mouth noises]

332
00:16:11,553 --> 00:16:13,722
-[male voice] <i>You've got mail.</i>
-Oh my God, I've got mail.

333
00:16:13,806 --> 00:16:15,724
Oh! This is thrilling.

334
00:16:15,808 --> 00:16:18,352
I mean, I've had kids,
but this is right up there.

335
00:16:19,144 --> 00:16:20,813
Actually, that's from me.

336
00:16:21,313 --> 00:16:24,525
There's something I've been trying
to tell you, so go ahead and open it.

337
00:16:24,608 --> 00:16:25,693
Oh?

338
00:16:25,776 --> 00:16:26,986
Okay.

339
00:16:27,861 --> 00:16:30,322
Double-click on the little mailbox.

340
00:16:32,074 --> 00:16:33,367
Oh dear.

341
00:16:33,450 --> 00:16:35,285
Where did it go?

342
00:16:35,995 --> 00:16:36,996
It's right there.

343
00:16:38,247 --> 00:16:39,081
Oh.

344
00:16:39,164 --> 00:16:40,332
-Click-click!
-[mouse clicks]

345
00:16:40,416 --> 00:16:42,501
No. The little box in the corner.

346
00:16:43,085 --> 00:16:44,837
-The whole thing is gone.
-It's behind there.

347
00:16:44,920 --> 00:16:46,338
-Behind where?
-That window.

348
00:16:46,422 --> 00:16:48,590
[loud computer chime]

349
00:16:48,674 --> 00:16:49,675
[Ozzie huffs]

350
00:16:51,635 --> 00:16:52,845
Restarting. So…

351
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:56,473
We have about five minutes.

352
00:16:57,850 --> 00:16:58,809
[sighs]

353
00:16:58,892 --> 00:16:59,893
Forget it.

354
00:17:01,270 --> 00:17:02,229
Mrs. Forman.

355
00:17:03,105 --> 00:17:03,939
I'm gay.

356
00:17:05,232 --> 00:17:07,985
I've known for a while now,
and I wanted you to know.

357
00:17:08,068 --> 00:17:10,738
I even have a boyfriend,
Etienne, who lives in Canada.

358
00:17:12,406 --> 00:17:14,241
Well, I don't know how I feel about this.

359
00:17:14,992 --> 00:17:15,826
Oh.

360
00:17:16,410 --> 00:17:19,371
My friend Sharon married a Canadian man,

361
00:17:19,455 --> 00:17:22,041
and he made off with her Toyota wagon.

362
00:17:22,124 --> 00:17:26,086
And her cat's ashes were in there,
and she is a mess.

363
00:17:28,213 --> 00:17:30,632
But… you're okay with me being gay?

364
00:17:30,716 --> 00:17:32,092
Well, of course I am.

365
00:17:33,260 --> 00:17:36,430
Oh, sweet boy, get in here.

366
00:17:39,224 --> 00:17:42,227
You just made me feel really special.

367
00:17:43,353 --> 00:17:44,396
[chuckles softly]

368
00:17:47,608 --> 00:17:49,193
[inhales, exhales sharply]

369
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:52,696
Is that why you helped me
with the computer?

370
00:17:53,447 --> 00:17:55,532
No, I did it because I loved it.

371
00:17:56,408 --> 00:17:58,327
[laughs giddily]

372
00:17:59,912 --> 00:18:03,040
[rock music playing]

373
00:18:07,002 --> 00:18:09,755
So… yesterday, huh?

374
00:18:10,631 --> 00:18:11,882
Very unexpected.

375
00:18:13,175 --> 00:18:14,009
Did we…?

376
00:18:14,676 --> 00:18:16,011
Have fun? Yeah.

377
00:18:16,553 --> 00:18:17,554
We did.

378
00:18:18,180 --> 00:18:19,014
Twice.

379
00:18:20,390 --> 00:18:22,601
-Let's never talk about this again.
-Secret dies with me.

380
00:18:24,478 --> 00:18:25,729
Sit here, Nik.

381
00:18:25,813 --> 00:18:28,023
I'm gonna take this lettuce
out to my goat.

382
00:18:28,982 --> 00:18:29,817
You did not.

383
00:18:29,900 --> 00:18:31,860
It was free, Nik!

384
00:18:33,070 --> 00:18:34,822
You're a goat's mommy now.

385
00:18:35,447 --> 00:18:36,824
Okay, that's cute.

386
00:18:38,826 --> 00:18:41,453
So, step seven is in the books.
What's next?

387
00:18:41,537 --> 00:18:42,746
-I steal a car.
-Really?

388
00:18:42,830 --> 00:18:44,540
No, I tell my pediatrician.

389
00:18:46,917 --> 00:18:49,002
Oh God. Jay just walked in.

390
00:18:49,086 --> 00:18:50,796
He's wearing that tiny T-shirt.

391
00:18:52,131 --> 00:18:54,550
Oh my God. He's even hotter
when he's tired.

392
00:18:55,968 --> 00:18:57,761
How long do I keep
this friend thing going?

393
00:18:57,845 --> 00:19:00,347
I don't know. It was your crazy-ass idea.

394
00:19:02,099 --> 00:19:03,183
Just go talk to him.

395
00:19:03,267 --> 00:19:04,434
What am I supposed to do?

396
00:19:04,518 --> 00:19:07,604
Profess my love to him in front of
the ketchup pump? That's so scary.

397
00:19:07,688 --> 00:19:10,607
I just came out to your grandma.
You can tell a guy who knows you like him

398
00:19:10,691 --> 00:19:11,525
that you like him.

399
00:19:14,778 --> 00:19:17,197
-Is that Nikki's scrunchie?
-What?!

400
00:19:17,698 --> 00:19:18,866
No. [nervous chuckle]

401
00:19:19,575 --> 00:19:20,492
Hey.

402
00:19:21,243 --> 00:19:22,119
Hey.

403
00:19:22,202 --> 00:19:25,664
Um, so you know how the other night
I said I just wanted to be friends?

404
00:19:25,747 --> 00:19:28,125
Yeah. That was a surprise,
and not the fun kind.

405
00:19:29,710 --> 00:19:31,962
Well, then you're gonna like
what I'm about to say.

406
00:19:32,045 --> 00:19:33,797
Sorry. It took me forever to park.

407
00:19:33,881 --> 00:19:36,091
Your friend is chasing a goat
around the parking lot

408
00:19:36,175 --> 00:19:37,384
while some girl yells at him.

409
00:19:38,886 --> 00:19:40,971
At least we'll have a story
for our first date.

410
00:19:43,557 --> 00:19:45,017
Oh, Serena, this is my friend Leia.

411
00:19:45,100 --> 00:19:46,185
Howdy, friend!

412
00:19:48,729 --> 00:19:52,107
I was, uh, just getting some ketchup
from the big ol' pump.

413
00:19:57,362 --> 00:19:58,363
Red?

414
00:20:01,241 --> 00:20:02,367
What are you doing?

415
00:20:03,577 --> 00:20:04,536
Uh…

416
00:20:04,620 --> 00:20:06,163
Nothing. Go back to bed.

417
00:20:06,872 --> 00:20:09,249
Red Forman, move your hands.

418
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:10,918
[Red groans]

419
00:20:15,672 --> 00:20:17,007
Is that Raquel Welch?

420
00:20:21,929 --> 00:20:23,722
[gasps] It is!

421
00:20:25,807 --> 00:20:26,808
Red Forman.

422
00:20:28,602 --> 00:20:32,022
I am so happy
you're using the new computer!

423
00:20:33,565 --> 00:20:35,609
Now, find me one of Kirk Douglas.

424
00:20:36,693 --> 00:20:37,611
[Red clears throat]

425
00:20:37,694 --> 00:20:40,113
-In his gladiator outfit.
-Oh… Okay…

426
00:20:41,573 --> 00:20:42,616
Have at it.

427
00:20:44,326 --> 00:20:45,494
[clicking mouse]

428
00:20:45,577 --> 00:20:46,662
[loud computer chime]

429
00:20:46,745 --> 00:20:47,871
Restarting.

430
00:20:50,165 --> 00:20:53,085
[rock music playing]

